{"title": "Penobscot Man", "description": "The Penobscot Man is a collection of true stories about the river drivers, guides, and woodsmen of Maine\u2019s Penobscot River. Fannie Hardy Eckstorm writes from a firsthand knowledge of the region. The book portrays the men's dangerous log\u2011driving work, their courage and hardships, and the local legends and characters that shaped life along the river. Note: Occasionally, somewhat racist remarks or characterizations make their way into the narrative, reflecting the biases of the era. (Summary by John Greenman)", "duration": 23508, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "2225", "name": "Fannie Hardy Eckstorm"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/penobscotman_2602_librivox/penobscotman_2602.jpg", "copyright_year": "1904", "genres": ["*Non-fiction", "Social Science (Culture & Anthropology)", "Modern (19th C)"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "John Greenman"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "John Greenman"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "MaryAnn"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Zanyar"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Introductory", "readers": [107], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/penobscotman_2602_librivox/penobscotman_00_eckstorm_64kb.mp3", "duration": 390}, {"section": 1, "title": "Ch. I - Lugging Boat on Sowadnehunk", "readers": [107], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/penobscotman_2602_librivox/penobscotman_01_eckstorm_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1492}, {"section": 2, "title": "Ch. II - The Grim Tale of Larry Connors", "readers": [107], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/penobscotman_2602_librivox/penobscotman_02_eckstorm_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1815}, {"section": 3, "title": "Ch. III - Hymns before Battle", "readers": [107], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/penobscotman_2602_librivox/penobscotman_03_eckstorm_64kb.mp3", "duration": 864}, {"section": 4, "title": "Ch. IV - The Death of Thoreau's Guide", "readers": [107], "path": "https://ww